20 November 2019 - Julius Malema and Mbuyiseni Ndlozi appear in the Randburg Magistrate's court on charges of assault against a policeman. JOHANNESBURG - EFF leader Julius Malema and party MP Mbuyseni Ndlozi are back in court on Tuesday morning. They are charged with allegedly assaulting a police colonel at the 2018 funeral of Winnie Madikizela-Mandela. READ: DA to lay criminal charges against Malema The alleged April 2018 assault was caught on CCTV camera and released by the lobby group AfriForum late last year. Malema and Ndlozi previously said that the case was a waste of time.